WEBVTT

00:00.635 --> 00:02.789
While some businesses are turning cautious...

00:02.860 --> 00:04.975
...in the face of global economic gloom,...

00:05.160 --> 00:09.118
...Ikea is banking on consumers searching for more value for money.

00:10.113 --> 00:16.019
Its owners, Inca Group, is spending 3.2 billion dollars through 2023,...

00:16.502 --> 00:19.155
...much of it to modify its out of town outlets...

00:19.381 --> 00:22.155
...so they can also handle e-commerce distribution.

00:23.039 --> 00:26.569
A third of the cash is earmarked for London and the UK,...

00:27.039 --> 00:30.035
...a test bed for new store formats and logistics.

00:30.683 --> 00:34.710
Inca wants to invest in automation and ship online purchases...

00:34.900 --> 00:36.859
...directly from certain stores,...

00:37.361 --> 00:41.817
...which they say will make deliveries faster, cheaper and lower emissions.

00:42.625 --> 00:45.521
Over the past two years of disruption and lockdowns,...

00:45.712 --> 00:49.361
...Ikea saw record demand for its cut-price home furnishings.

00:49.620 --> 00:52.290
It's already invested over 2 billion dollars...

00:52.472 --> 00:55.083
...while adapting to the rise in online shopping.

00:56.591 --> 00:59.555
And now, as customers feel the spending squeeze,...

00:59.863 --> 01:03.054
...Inca says that timing for Ikea couldn't be better.

